h2. Early Relationships

bq.. &ldquo;What gives the parent a special place in the young child's life? What does the close emotional relationship with the parent provide that other adults cannot replicate? 

&ldquo;To answer such questions, researchers have focused on the development of security, confidence, and trust between infants and toddlers and their parents. This central feature of early relationships is captured by the concept of *&ldquo;attachment security.&rdquo;* 

&ldquo;In the rare situations in which infants do not have the opportunity to form an attachment with even one trusted adult, their development can deteriorate rapidly and dramatically.

&ldquo;The remarkable recovery that these infants display once they receive stable care and loving attention further reveals the importance of the child's earliest intimate relationships.&rdquo;

p. From "Neurons to Neighborhoods: The Science of Early Childhood Development":http://babyutoledo.com/needlink/ (2000)


